===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|豹|皃|c1=p|abb1=y|c2=s|t2=looks|ls=psc}}.

Originally written as {{och-l|皃}}, which is a {{liushu|p|nocap=1}} of the face.

===Etymology===
Note a very strong formal match with {{cog|my|မြောက်|t=to reach the apex, be consummated}}. Though the semantic gap is non-trivial, a sense relation "reach the top" > "that which exists on the top or surface" > "outward appearance, expression" appears feasible.

